00:00:00.206 --> 00:00:01.450
- [Instructor] In this
video, we're going to try

00:00:01.450 --> 00:00:04.104
to get a sense of what the
limit as x approaches three

00:00:04.104 --> 00:00:06.423
of x to the third minus 3x squared

00:00:06.423 --> 00:00:08.090
over 5x minus 15 is.

00:00:10.143 --> 00:00:12.461
And when I say get a sense,
we're going to do that

00:00:12.461 --> 00:00:17.238
by seeing what values for
this expression we get

00:00:17.238 --> 00:00:20.126
as x gets closer and closer to three.

00:00:20.126 --> 00:00:21.987
Now, one thing that you
might want to try out,

00:00:21.987 --> 00:00:24.104
is, well, what happens to this expression

00:00:24.104 --> 00:00:26.534
when x is equal to three?

00:00:26.534 --> 00:00:29.362
Well, then, it's going to
be three to the third power

00:00:29.362 --> 00:00:31.988
minus three times three squared

00:00:31.988 --> 00:00:34.571
over five times three minus 15.

00:00:36.393 --> 00:00:39.257
So at x equals three, this
expression's going to be,

00:00:39.257 --> 00:00:41.719
and let's see, in the
numerator, you have 27 minus 27,

00:00:41.719 --> 00:00:44.552
zero, over 15 minus 15, over zero.

00:00:45.552 --> 00:00:47.030
So this expression is actually

00:00:47.030 --> 00:00:50.200
not defined as x equals three.

00:00:50.200 --> 00:00:51.533
We get this indeterminate form.

00:00:51.533 --> 00:00:54.008
We get zero over zero.

00:00:54.008 --> 00:00:55.644
But let's see, even though the function,

00:00:55.644 --> 00:00:57.648
even though the expression is not defined,

00:00:57.648 --> 00:01:01.902
let's see if we can get a sense
of what the limit might be.

00:01:01.902 --> 00:01:05.291
And to do that, I'm
going to set up a table.

00:01:05.291 --> 00:01:07.874
So, let me set up a table here.

00:01:08.759 --> 00:01:11.118
And actually I'm going
to set up two tables.

00:01:11.118 --> 00:01:14.868
So this is x and this is x to the third

00:01:16.327 --> 00:01:19.160
minus 3x squared over 5x minus 15.

00:01:23.373 --> 00:01:24.889
Actually, I'm going to do that again,

00:01:24.889 --> 00:01:27.273
and I'll tell you why in a second.

00:01:27.273 --> 00:01:31.460
So, this is gonna be x,
and this is x to the third

00:01:31.460 --> 00:01:34.293
minus 3x squared over 5x minus 15.

00:01:37.319 --> 00:01:38.473
The reason why I set up two tables,

00:01:38.473 --> 00:01:39.538
I didn't have to do two tables.

00:01:39.538 --> 00:01:40.917
I could have done it all in one table,

00:01:40.917 --> 00:01:42.301
but hopefully, this will make it

00:01:42.301 --> 00:01:44.195
a little bit more intuitive
what I'm trying to do,

00:01:44.195 --> 00:01:46.575
is on this left table,

00:01:46.575 --> 00:01:48.307
I'm gonna, let's try out x values

00:01:48.307 --> 00:01:50.628
that get closer and close to three

00:01:50.628 --> 00:01:54.077
from the left, from values
that are less than three.

00:01:54.077 --> 00:01:57.198
So for example, we could
go to 2.9 and figure out

00:01:57.198 --> 00:01:59.967
what the expression equals
when x is 2.9, but then

00:01:59.967 --> 00:02:01.611
we could try to get even a
little bit closer than that.

00:02:01.611 --> 00:02:03.278
We could go to 2.99,

00:02:05.699 --> 00:02:07.259
