even closer than that.

00:02:07.259 --> 00:02:11.426
We could go to 2.999, and so,
one way to think about it here

00:02:13.264 --> 00:02:16.114
is as we try to figure out
what this expression equals

00:02:16.114 --> 00:02:18.325
as we get closer and closer to three,

00:02:18.325 --> 00:02:22.308
we're trying to approximate
the limit from the left.

00:02:22.308 --> 00:02:24.308
So, limit from the left.

00:02:28.324 --> 00:02:29.582
And why do I say the left?

00:02:29.582 --> 00:02:32.028
Well, if you would think about
this on a coordinate plane,

00:02:32.028 --> 00:02:34.330
these are the x values, so
they're to the left of three,

00:02:34.330 --> 00:02:36.232
but we're getting closer
and closer and closer.

00:02:36.232 --> 00:02:37.443
We're moving to the right,

00:02:37.443 --> 00:02:40.547
but these are the x values
that are on the left side

00:02:40.547 --> 00:02:42.424
of three, that are less than three.

00:02:42.424 --> 00:02:44.729
But we also, in order
for the limit to exist,

00:02:44.729 --> 00:02:47.691
we have to be approaching the
same thing from both sides,

00:02:47.691 --> 00:02:49.438
from both the left and the right.

00:02:49.438 --> 00:02:51.120
So we could also try to approximate

00:02:51.120 --> 00:02:53.203
the limit from the right,

00:02:54.745 --> 00:02:56.896
and so what values would those be?

00:02:56.896 --> 00:03:00.449
Well, those would be x
values larger than three,

00:03:00.449 --> 00:03:02.612
so we could say 3.1,

00:03:02.612 --> 00:03:03.912
but then we might wanna
get a little bit closer.

00:03:03.912 --> 00:03:06.261
We could go 3.01, but
